article.headline: S. Carolina St. 66, Coker 64
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. -- Jason Flagler made a jumper as time expired to lift South Carolina State to a 66-64 victory over Coker on Saturday night. With 12 seconds left in the game, Coker's Josh Poston hit a 3-pointer to tie the score at 64-64. The Bulldogs (4-2) then called a timeout with 10 seconds to go, setting up the play for Flagler. Jason Johnson led South Carolina State with a game-high 19 points, followed by 18 points and 12 rebounds from Flagler in the consolation game of the Liberty Thanksgiving Classic. Coker (3-5) led 33-27 at halftime before extending its lead to 38-27 on J.C. Hafner's layup with 18:13 left in the second half. The Bulldogs then went on an 18-2 run that spanned over seven minutes to claim a 45-40 lead. The Cobras were led by Poston with 16 points, Vatrick Thompson with 15 and Lukas Varga with 14 points and eight assists.
